def: A process of electric welding in which heat is developed by alarge current passing through the metal.
Of or pertaining to Dionysus or to the Dionysia; Bacchic; as, aDionysiac festival; the Dionysiac theater at Athens.
An instrument for measuring and recording automatically therise and fall of a river.
A white metallic alloy; which is made into spoons, forks,teapots, etc. British plate or German silver. See German silver,under German.
Funnel-shaped; -- applied particularly to a hollow muscleattached to the ball of the eye in many reptiles and mammals.
A collective term for the Welsh race; -- so called bythemselves . [Written also Cymri, Cwmry, Kymry, etc.]
Omission, inaccuracy, or defect in a record.
The office of a canon; a canonry.
Pertaining to, or obtained from, the doegling; as, doeglic acid(Chem.), an oily substance resembling oleic acid.
A pot containing melted tin into which the plates are dipped tobe coated.
Any gull living on the seacoast.
Occurring or appearing once every two weeks; fortnightly.-- n.
